        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Code verification via method of manufactured solutions at Gradation 4",
        "description": "Observed order of accuracy must be within 10% of theoretical order for all governing equations using the Method of Manufactured Solutions (MMS) on at least three systematically refined grids. Achieved: MMS convergence studies confirm 1.92 observed order (theoretical 2.0) for momentum and 1.88 for scalar transport; results documented in verification report VR-2025-04."
      },
      "rationale": "MRL 5 requires rigorous code verification. MMS studies on three grid levels confirm near-second-order convergence for momentum and scalar transport equations, satisfying Gradation 4 requirements."
