        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "GCI-based discretization error estimate < 2% on QoI at Gradation 4",
        "description": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) must be computed on at least three systematically refined meshes; the fine-grid GCI on the primary QoI (NIH) must be below 2%. Achieved: GCI fine = 1.4% on NIH across all 5 operating points; Richardson extrapolation confirms monotonic convergence."
      },
      "rationale": "Three-mesh GCI study yields fine-grid GCI of 1.4% on NIH, meeting the Gradation 4 threshold of < 2% for a Class III MRL 5 device."
