        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Turbulence and hemolysis sub-model selection justified with sensitivity analysis at Gradation 4",
        "description": "The choice of turbulence closure (SST k-ω) and power-law hemolysis model must be justified by comparison against at least two alternative model forms; sensitivity of NIH to model-form choice must be quantified and shown to be within experimental uncertainty. Achieved: SST k-ω compared against realizable k-ε and LES; power-law hemolysis model compared against Giersiepen correlation; NIH sensitivity to model form is 8.2%, within experimental uncertainty of 12%."
      },
      "rationale": "Model-form sensitivity study comparing three turbulence closures and two hemolysis sub-models shows NIH variation of 8.2%, within experimental uncertainty, justifying the selected model form at Gradation 4."
