        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Input uncertainty characterised via Monte Carlo at Gradation 4",
        "description": "All uncertain model inputs (fluid viscosity, density, inlet turbulence intensity, hemolysis model constants) must be characterised with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation (N ≥ 1000 samples) must produce 95% CI on NIH. Achieved: 1500-sample Monte Carlo on 6 input parameters; 95% CI on NIH is ±9.1% of mean; documented in UQ report UQ-2025-03."
      },
      "rationale": "1500-sample Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation over 6 uncertain inputs yields 95% CI of ±9.1% on NIH, satisfying Gradation 4 input uncertainty requirements at MRL 5."
