        "name": "Test fluid and pump specimen characterised and representative of clinical use at Gradation 4",
        "description": "Bovine blood or validated blood analogue must be characterised for viscosity and density at test conditions; pump specimen geometry must be CMM-verified against nominal CAD within 50 µm. Achieved: Porcine blood analogue (glycerol-water) characterised per ASTM F1841; pump specimen CMM-verified with maximum deviation of 32 µm documented in inspection report IR-2024-11."
      },
      "rationale": "Porcine blood analogue characterised per ASTM F1841; pump specimen CMM-verified to within 32 µm of nominal CAD, satisfying Gradation 4 test sample requirements."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-use-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "Use error as defined in ASME V&V 40 pertains to unintended or erroneous application of the simulation tool by an end-user in a clinical or operational context. In this assessment, the CFD model is operated exclusively by trained simulation engineers under a controlled SQA regime (see Software quality assurance factor); the model outputs are not directly operated by clinical end-users and are not exposed to point-of-care variability. The factor therefore does not apply to this COU and has been formally scoped out of the credibility assessment with concurrence from the regulatory strategy team (memo RSM-2025-01)."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/morrison-cou2-equivalency-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters is relevant when a model is transferred from a validation context to a distinct COU context with different input parameter ranges, requiring a formal equivalency argument. In this assessment, the validation activities were conducted directly at COU-representative conditions using the same pump geometry, the same operating envelope, and the same fluid properties as the intended deployment (see Relevance of validation activities factor). There is no transfer gap between validation and COU input spaces; consequently, a separate equivalency assessment would be redundant and the factor is not applicable. This determination is documented in assessment rationale memo ARM-2025-02."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-nc6-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All eleven assessed credibility factors achieve requiredLevel 4, meeting or exceeding the MRL 5 thresholds established in the Morrison V&V 40 framework. The two not-applicable factors (Use error and Equivalency of input parameters) have documented rationale confirming they do not apply to this COU: use error is excluded because the model is operated solely by trained engineers under formal SQA controls; equivalency of input parameters is excluded because validation was conducted directly at COU-representative conditions with no transfer gap. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification (1500 samples) yields a 95% CI of ±9.1% on NIH; combined simulation and experimental uncertainty bands overlap at all five operating points with E_rms = 11.3%. The provenance chain is complete from foundational experimental datasets through validation activities to this assurance package. The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD model provides sufficient credibility for regulatory submission supporting the Class III VAD hemolysis claim.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
